WEBVTT

00:00:04.755 --> 00:00:09.927
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.803 --> 00:00:13.806
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.932 --> 00:00:16.600
At least it is true...

00:00:17.143 --> 00:00:20.771
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:22.648 --> 00:00:24.025
G-Guts?

00:00:24.734 --> 00:00:26.152
Commander Guts?

00:00:26.902 --> 00:00:28.863
Is it really you, Commander Guts?

00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:30.406
Commander Guts!

00:00:30.531 --> 00:00:31.782
Commander Guts!

00:00:56.724 --> 00:00:58.809
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:00:58.976 --> 00:01:00.728
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:00.936 --> 00:01:04.440
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:06.901
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:07.026 --> 00:01:08.944
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:09.070 --> 00:01:11.155
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:11.322 --> 00:01:12.948
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:13.199 --> 00:01:16.660
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:17.286 --> 00:01:20.206
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:21.082 --> 00:01:21.665
<i>I...</i>

00:01:22.041 --> 00:01:22.792
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:22.917 --> 00:01:24.919
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:25.086 --> 00:01:25.961
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:26.087 --> 00:01:26.921
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:27.088 --> 00:01:28.714
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:28.964 --> 00:01:29.924
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:30.091 --> 00:01:30.841
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:30.966 --> 00:01:32.843
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:33.094 --> 00:01:33.969
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:34.178 --> 00:01:34.970
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:35.221 --> 00:01:36.597
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:36.931 --> 00:01:37.973
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:38.182 --> 00:01:39.100
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:39.225 --> 00:01:39.850
<i>Too late...</i>

00:01:39.975 --> 00:01:41.477
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:01:46.607 --> 00:01:50.611
Confession

00:01:53.989 --> 00:01:54.865
Guts...

00:01:55.324 --> 00:01:56.367
Guts?

00:01:56.492 --> 00:01:57.493
Is it possible?

00:01:57.618 --> 00:01:59.453
The legendary commander...

00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:01.705
There's no time to waste.

00:02:01.872 --> 00:02:03.582
Don't you have a job to do?

00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:12.258
Don't back off!

00:02:12.383 --> 00:02:14.760
Position in battle
formations and counter attack!

00:02:22.143 --> 00:02:23.435
That commander is nothing!

00:02:23.561 --> 00:02:24.645
Their numbers are small.

00:02:24.687 --> 00:02:26.063
Advance, advance forward!

00:03:03.809 --> 00:03:04.852
Those eyes...

00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:06.353
They haven't changed.

00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:09.940
It's no use, we don't stand a chance.

00:03:10.065 --> 00:03:11.358
Dammit!

00:03:11.567 --> 00:03:13.110
There's no choice, retreat!

00:03:15.362 --> 00:03:16.989
Don't let them get away!

00:03:17.114 --> 00:03:18.574
Stop, don't jeopardize yourself!

00:03:18.699 --> 00:03:19.825
But, we can't...

00:03:19.992 --> 00:03:20.951
Guts!

00:03:22.244 --> 00:03:23.746
What the hell, guys!

00:03:28.626 --> 00:03:29.627
Guts!

00:03:29.835 --> 00:03:32.004
Hey, you're looking good, little guy.

00:03:32.254 --> 00:03:34.256
G-Guts...

00:03:41.847 --> 00:03:42.765
Commander!

00:03:42.848 --> 00:03:44.099
Commander Guts!

00:03:44.642 --> 00:03:45.893
I knew it!

00:03:46.018 --> 00:03:48.020
I knew you'd come back someday!

00:03:49.772 --> 00:03:50.648
You guys...

00:03:57.780 --> 00:03:59.782
We don't have any time to waste.

00:04:00.115 --> 00:04:01.283
The enemy will return.

00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:03.285
We must mobilize while it's dark.

00:04:04.036 --> 00:04:05.037
Caska...

00:04:05.412 --> 00:04:06.538
Do as she says.

00:04:06.997 --> 00:04:09.416
We must move quickly
now, we'll catch up later.

00:04:21.887 --> 00:04:25.599
In this past year the Hawks has been
cut down to a fifth of its original size...

00:04:26.976 --> 00:04:30.646
We can't even call
ourselves an army anymore...

00:04:32.231 --> 00:04:34.775
Even so, it could be worse...

00:04:35.234 --> 00:04:39.780
Without Caska there'd be
nothing left of the Band of Hawk...

00:04:42.283 --> 00:04:44.910
On that fateful day, a year ago...

00:04:47.162 --> 00:04:50.791
We all gathered under Griffith's order.

00:04:51.625 --> 00:04:54.169
We hadn't ridden our horses in a while.

00:04:54.545 --> 00:04:57.423
We waited with a kind of
excitement in our hearts.

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:03.554
Where is Griffith?

00:05:19.945 --> 00:05:21.322
Everybody, get down!

00:05:25.534 --> 00:05:28.704
All of a sudden, arrows
came pouring down on us like rain.

00:05:29.163 --> 00:05:30.789
It was the Midland army...

00:05:30.956 --> 00:05:32.791
All was confusion and chaos...

00:05:34.585 --> 00:05:36.837
We found out only
after we had escaped...

00:05:37.588 --> 00:05:40.424
...that Griffith had been
captured and arrested for treason.

00:05:43.719 --> 00:05:44.845
Griffith?

00:05:45.721 --> 00:05:46.805
A year ago...

00:05:46.972 --> 00:05:48.974
It was the clay after you left.

00:05:50.184 --> 00:05:51.810
I can't believe it...

00:05:52.353 --> 00:05:53.854
The Griffith we knew...

00:05:54.104 --> 00:05:54.980
Why?

00:05:55.314 --> 00:05:57.066
After you left, Guts...

00:05:57.566 --> 00:05:59.860
Griffith was very depressed...

00:06:00.986 --> 00:06:04.448
I think that maybe because you left...

00:06:11.497 --> 00:06:12.956
Don't flatter yourself...

00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:17.461
What happened to Griffith has
absolutely nothing to do with you.

00:06:17.878 --> 00:06:18.754
Nothing.

00:06:20.964 --> 00:06:23.217
But, you should have seen
how Caska came through!

00:06:23.384 --> 00:06:26.887
She fought and got us through to the
end with wounds in five different places.

00:06:27.888 --> 00:06:31.517
We welcomed Caska
as the leader of the Hawks...

00:06:32.601 --> 00:06:33.977
But it's amazing...

00:06:34.103 --> 00:06:35.896
You coming back when
we need you the most...

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:38.107
It goes to show we still have luck.

00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:43.404
We've been planning an operation,
and we're about to carry it out

00:06:43.904 --> 00:06:44.738
An operation?

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:47.908
We're going to rescue Griffith.

00:06:56.166 --> 00:06:58.502
The guys that are
left here are worn out...

00:06:58.919 --> 00:07:01.296
Their hearts and
bodies covered in wounds...

00:07:01.547 --> 00:07:04.675
But not one of them will
even consider leaving us...

00:07:05.134 --> 00:07:07.803
Even though no one
is telling them to stay...

00:07:08.554 --> 00:07:11.640
We'll never see the end of this
with just courage and will...

00:07:12.516 --> 00:07:17.062
The ones who have stayed are
true Hawks, right down to the bone...

00:07:17.521 --> 00:07:19.314
We're not just rescuing Griffith...

00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:21.817
You see, without Griffith there is no...

00:07:22.317 --> 00:07:23.318
Band of the Hawk.

00:07:29.825 --> 00:07:31.034
It's good to be back...

00:07:31.577 --> 00:07:33.704
Some things never change.

00:07:33.912 --> 00:07:35.414
We're counting on you...

00:07:35.539 --> 00:07:36.540
...Commander Guts.

00:07:36.957 --> 00:07:38.959
He's not a commander anymore.

00:07:39.334 --> 00:07:40.335
Corkus...

00:07:40.586 --> 00:07:44.590
That bastard left us
when we needed him the most!

00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:47.468
How can you call
that betrayer one of us?

00:07:47.718 --> 00:07:49.178
Corkus, how can you?

00:07:49.720 --> 00:07:52.431
This is your true
self, Guts the betrayer...

00:07:52.556 --> 00:07:54.975
At least make the distinction clear.

00:07:56.560 --> 00:07:57.311
Yeah...

00:07:57.561 --> 00:07:58.312
I understand.

00:08:03.358 --> 00:08:04.109
Guts...

00:08:06.361 --> 00:08:07.613
Take care of...

00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:08.322
...Caska.

00:08:10.073 --> 00:08:12.242
That fateful day a year ago...

00:08:12.367 --> 00:08:16.205
Caska spent three long nights and
days lingering on the brink of death...

00:08:16.580 --> 00:08:19.875
In the throes of nightmares
she cried out, over and over...

00:08:20.876 --> 00:08:22.252
...for Griffith...

00:08:23.003 --> 00:08:24.505
...and you.

00:08:33.388 --> 00:08:36.308
She's pushing herself
more than she'll ever let on...

00:08:36.808 --> 00:08:37.684
That's why...

00:08:38.060 --> 00:08:39.686
...you've got to do something.

00:08:40.187 --> 00:08:42.189
We're not enough for her.

00:09:12.344 --> 00:09:14.596
Quite impressive...

00:09:14.972 --> 00:09:17.849
Your eyes are still shining with life...

00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:28.485
Don't worry.

00:09:28.610 --> 00:09:32.114
I'll stay away from your
vitals so you won't die.

00:09:32.239 --> 00:09:37.744
I've been ordered by the King to make
sure you live at least another three years.

00:09:44.251 --> 00:09:47.629
Youth can be so frightening...

00:09:47.754 --> 00:09:50.507
...or on the contrary,
a marvel to behold...

00:09:52.134 --> 00:09:56.263
However mankind must live
within his own means and abilities...

00:09:56.388 --> 00:10:00.267
It seems your
heroism was rather shallow...

00:10:03.604 --> 00:10:07.899
It's been bothering me, this
unusual charm you're wearing.

00:10:08.275 --> 00:10:12.029
But it has no meaning
if it can't protect you...

00:10:41.308 --> 00:10:42.934
Come here for a second...

00:10:49.191 --> 00:10:50.400
What is it?

00:10:52.402 --> 00:10:53.195
On guard.

00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:03.163
Hey, wait!

00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:05.666
I said wait!

00:11:14.299 --> 00:11:15.425
What the hell?

00:11:18.345 --> 00:11:19.471
Hey, stop!

00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:20.555
I mean it!

00:11:20.681 --> 00:11:21.348
Fight!

00:11:26.561 --> 00:11:27.938
What the hell's wrong with you?

00:11:27.979 --> 00:11:29.815
Is this how you greet someone?

00:11:30.232 --> 00:11:32.484
Do you expect me to
deal with this bullshit?

00:11:34.861 --> 00:11:37.364
Why the hell did you come back now?

00:11:38.990 --> 00:11:40.242
It's your fault!

00:11:40.617 --> 00:11:41.993
You destroyed everything!

00:11:43.078 --> 00:11:44.121
It's all your fault!

00:11:46.206 --> 00:11:47.124
Me?

00:11:47.249 --> 00:11:48.250
That's right...

00:11:48.375 --> 00:11:49.334
Griffith and...

00:11:49.501 --> 00:11:50.711
The Band of Hawk...

00:11:50.836 --> 00:11:51.878
Everything...

00:11:52.254 --> 00:11:54.005
You destroyed everything!

00:11:54.256 --> 00:11:55.006
Me?

00:11:55.132 --> 00:11:55.716
Why me?

00:11:57.008 --> 00:11:58.760
Because you left us...

00:11:59.261 --> 00:12:01.221
Because you left Griffith!

00:12:05.016 --> 00:12:06.643
That can't be right...

00:12:07.352 --> 00:12:08.770
It's Griffith...

00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:11.148
The Griffith we know...

00:12:11.982 --> 00:12:13.984
...being destroyed
by such a small thing...

00:12:15.026 --> 00:12:16.528
That can't be...

00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:20.282
You really are stupid...

00:12:20.490 --> 00:12:21.408
...aren't you?

00:12:26.538 --> 00:12:28.039
I told you before!

00:12:28.248 --> 00:12:30.542
When a man has the
desire for something great...

00:12:30.625 --> 00:12:33.170
...he must bear a great burden...

00:12:33.920 --> 00:12:34.880
Griffith...

00:12:35.422 --> 00:12:37.507
...had to become stronger...

00:12:38.925 --> 00:12:39.801
But...

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:42.179
Griffith is not a god...

00:12:42.304 --> 00:12:45.265
You can't grab the hearts of
men with ideals and dreams alone...

00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:48.310
It was you, who made Griffith weak!

00:12:50.937 --> 00:12:53.940
Griffith couldn't go on without you!

00:13:04.075 --> 00:13:05.160
It can't be...

00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:07.329
You could have dodged that...

00:13:10.207 --> 00:13:11.833
What should I have clone?

00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:18.215
L-Let go.

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:22.052
I did what I had to do, just like Griffith.

00:13:22.594 --> 00:13:23.970
That's enough, let go.

00:13:24.304 --> 00:13:26.973
I did what I had to, that's all.

00:13:28.099 --> 00:13:30.101
What else could I have done?

00:13:31.228 --> 00:13:32.354
Let go.

00:13:34.481 --> 00:13:36.483
All right, just let go!

00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:44.616
I know.

00:13:45.742 --> 00:13:47.077
I understand.

00:13:47.327 --> 00:13:48.119
The truth is...

00:13:49.371 --> 00:13:51.122
...you're right.

00:13:52.624 --> 00:13:55.460
But I can't take it...

00:13:57.754 --> 00:13:59.089
I can't bear it...

00:14:01.967 --> 00:14:07.389
If only I could change the way my
heart feels, it would be so much easier...

00:14:08.390 --> 00:14:10.016
I'm not stupid...

00:14:10.642 --> 00:14:12.769
I know that the quickest path...

00:14:13.019 --> 00:14:16.022
...to the throne of Midland is
through Princess Charlotte.

00:14:16.731 --> 00:14:18.275
I knew that all along.

00:14:19.276 --> 00:14:24.114
And I knew that if it was up to
Griffith, that was the path he would take.

00:14:25.282 --> 00:14:27.993
Somehow I thought I could take it.

00:14:28.535 --> 00:14:32.414
Even if I could not stand by
Griffith's side as a woman...

00:14:32.539 --> 00:14:34.499
...I thought I could
at least be his sword.

00:14:35.667 --> 00:14:37.752
...that's what I wanted to believe.

00:14:40.755 --> 00:14:43.633
But, that clay you left...

00:14:44.426 --> 00:14:46.386
...it was very clear to me.

00:14:48.263 --> 00:14:53.059
Those days I had spent by
Griffith's side were a thing of the past...

00:14:53.768 --> 00:14:57.272
My dream had already ended.

00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:02.652
The reason why I have
been protecting the Hawks...

00:15:02.819 --> 00:15:05.322
...may just be a small thing, but...

00:15:05.530 --> 00:15:08.825
...I may lose myself
unless I cling on to what I have.

00:15:09.826 --> 00:15:12.412
But, it doesn't matter now.

00:15:14.080 --> 00:15:15.707
I can't be a woman...

00:15:16.207 --> 00:15:18.335
...or anything special...

00:15:19.169 --> 00:15:24.674
Fulfilling the dream of a man I
don't even know is dead or alive...

00:15:25.467 --> 00:15:27.594
I don't know anymore.

00:15:29.179 --> 00:15:30.722
I'm so tired...

00:15:31.598 --> 00:15:32.974
You do the rest...

00:15:33.224 --> 00:15:33.683
Caska?

00:16:01.836 --> 00:16:02.629
Damn it!

00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:04.130
What are you thinking?

00:16:04.255 --> 00:16:04.965
Listen to me!

00:16:05.006 --> 00:16:06.967
Don't go near that cliff again!

00:16:07.133 --> 00:16:09.469
I can't afford to be
dragged down with you!

00:16:09.761 --> 00:16:10.595
Understood?

00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:13.014
Silly.

00:16:13.515 --> 00:16:14.516
What?

00:16:24.484 --> 00:16:26.903
You're always hurt somewhere...

00:16:27.779 --> 00:16:30.907
Always shedding
blood because of me...

00:16:31.408 --> 00:16:32.367
Hey...

00:16:34.744 --> 00:16:35.787
...silly...

00:16:37.622 --> 00:16:38.540
...so silly.

00:16:56.808 --> 00:16:59.894
That clay you left, I knew it then.

00:17:01.187 --> 00:17:05.233
I watched you walk away from Griffith, as
he slumped to his knees for the first time.

00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:08.028
You didn't look back once...

00:17:08.153 --> 00:17:11.740
And I couldn't accept
myself as a woman who was...

00:17:14.159 --> 00:17:16.411
...unable to take her eyes off you.

00:17:17.412 --> 00:17:20.665
If I did, I felt my whole life
since the moment I met Griffith...

00:17:20.749 --> 00:17:22.876
...would have all been a lie.

00:17:24.669 --> 00:17:27.172
My life had been one without deceit.

00:17:27.797 --> 00:17:30.425
That was my only pride...

00:17:31.551 --> 00:17:34.888
Because that was the
gift Griffith gave to me...

00:17:36.181 --> 00:17:37.015
But...

00:17:43.897 --> 00:17:45.315
I can change...

00:17:46.816 --> 00:17:50.653
There may be a place
for me in this man's soul...

00:17:52.697 --> 00:17:54.908
Instead of just receiving from him...

00:17:55.575 --> 00:17:58.328
I may be able to give
him something of worth.

00:18:05.794 --> 00:18:06.711
Guts...

00:18:07.045 --> 00:18:08.922
...aren't you going to Stay?

00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:13.843
Rescue Griffith and be like old times...

00:18:14.928 --> 00:18:16.096
No, I can't.

00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:18.681
I want to be very clear about this...

00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:26.106
I will stay until we rescue Griffith
and get the Hawks back on their feet...

00:18:26.356 --> 00:18:28.108
...but that's it...

00:18:28.358 --> 00:18:29.984
I must continue my journey...

00:18:31.361 --> 00:18:33.738
I will not draw my sword for others...

00:18:33.988 --> 00:18:35.990
...or be dangled by
another man's dream...

00:18:36.699 --> 00:18:39.369
From now on, I will
fight my own battles.

00:18:49.337 --> 00:18:50.839
My, my...

00:18:51.005 --> 00:18:52.340
How honorable...

00:18:55.343 --> 00:18:57.387
You're just like Griffith!

00:18:57.971 --> 00:18:59.139
Your dream is everything!

00:18:59.264 --> 00:19:00.765
It's always about you!

00:19:01.015 --> 00:19:03.393
It doesn't matter to
you if I'm here or not!

00:19:04.269 --> 00:19:04.978
Hey!

00:19:05.019 --> 00:19:06.146
Just go!

00:19:06.896 --> 00:19:09.149
Do what you want!

00:19:10.108 --> 00:19:13.027
Wind up dead somewhere,
alone with your sword.

00:19:16.781 --> 00:19:17.407
Come.

00:19:17.615 --> 00:19:18.408
What?

00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:20.994
Come with me.

00:19:24.539 --> 00:19:26.624
I don't know what the future will bring...

00:19:27.292 --> 00:19:31.004
All I know is I want to keep holding you...

00:19:31.421 --> 00:19:32.297
Stupid...

00:19:32.505 --> 00:19:34.382
I want to make love to you a hundred...

00:19:34.507 --> 00:19:36.759
...no a thousand times more...

00:19:37.927 --> 00:19:39.804
...that's how I feel right now.

00:19:40.680 --> 00:19:41.639
Stupid...

00:20:19.719 --> 00:20:20.970
What the...

00:20:55.755 --> 00:20:59.384
If it weren't for my arm,
I could have gone with you guys.

00:20:59.759 --> 00:21:01.719
Don't be sad...

00:21:01.886 --> 00:21:05.014
You'll be the first one to get a hug
from Griffith when he comes back.

00:21:06.015 --> 00:21:07.475
I'm counting on you Guts.

00:21:07.642 --> 00:21:09.602
Promise you'll bring him back safe.

00:21:09.894 --> 00:21:10.770
Yeah.

00:21:11.229 --> 00:21:12.522
On your horses!

00:21:19.279 --> 00:21:22.615
We will divide into two formations
and follow our respective plans.

00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:25.868
Griffith's rescue
operation will depart now!

00:21:26.035 --> 00:21:27.412
Let's go Boss!

00:21:32.125 --> 00:21:33.543
Rescue Operation!

00:21:33.793 --> 00:21:35.670
Depart for Midland!

00:22:02.572 --> 00:22:04.699
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:04.824 --> 00:22:08.328
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.579 --> 00:22:12.415
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.457 --> 00:22:15.335
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.086 --> 00:22:18.588
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:18.713 --> 00:22:19.839
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:23.051
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.344 --> 00:22:27.221
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.347 --> 00:22:30.558
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:34.187
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.604 --> 00:22:37.565
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.232 --> 00:22:41.235
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.111 --> 00:22:44.947
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:09.639 --> 00:23:12.475
Wandering through the
never-ending darkness...

00:23:13.393 --> 00:23:15.478
Deep in the hearts
of those who quest...

00:23:15.728 --> 00:23:18.398
What will keep their final flame burning?

00:23:18.731 --> 00:23:20.149
Will it be faith?

00:23:20.525 --> 00:23:21.984
Hatred?

00:23:22.402 --> 00:23:23.778
Or true love?

00:23:24.737 --> 00:23:30.535
